    base:desc "The Digital Twin constellation is orchestrated through a multi‑layer model‑based systems engineering (MBSE) architecture. Functional and logical abstractions are realised with SysML Interaction‑Block Diagrams (IBDs) or through architecture description languages such as ACME, AADL, or MontiArc. Behavioral dynamics are encoded in MontiArc Automaton, SysML state machines, or embedded MATLAB/Simulink. These models are transformed and synchronised via a common metamodel to generate executable artefacts in C++ or Java, which are then deployed as runtime components. The constellation manages resource allocation, simulation scheduling, and consistency checks across the distributed models, thereby enabling coordinated operation of the digital twin subsystems."
