instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "Digital Twin lifecycle is organized into the following MBSE phases: 1) Requirements Modeling – captured via SysML requirement diagrams; 2) Functional Architecture – expressed in SysML Block Definition and Internal Block Diagrams, and by ADLs such as ACME or AADL components; 3) Logical Architecture – further decomposed with MontiArc automaton/state‑machine constructs; 4) Product/Technical Implementation – implemented through Simulink models, MATLAB code, or general‑purpose languages such as C++/Java. Transition between phases is achieved by model transformation and integration of heterogeneous notations, enabling traceability across abstraction layers. Lifecycle governance is implicitly supported by MBSE best practices and the use of consistent modeling languages, though an explicit governance framework is not described."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "Horizontal integration is achieved by composing heterogeneous modeling and simulation frameworks. The system imports SysML, AADL, MontiArc, and Simulink artefacts and integrates them through model‑to‑model and model‑to‑code transformations. Generated code in C++/Java exposes services that can be consumed by enterprise applications. Integration patterns include synchronous model updates, API‑based data exchange, and runtime coupling of simulation engines with external analytics or control services. This approach enables the digital twin to interoperate with other enterprise systems using the standard MBSE toolchain and shared APIs."
]
